# LLM Wiki System Integration

This project uses a federated wiki system for agent knowledge management. You can search, ingest, export, and govern the wiki directly from Cursor.

## Quick Commands

Use these commands in Cursor's AI chat:

### Search Wiki
```
@wiki <query> [--domain DOMAIN] [--kind KIND] [--tags TAG1,TAG2]
```

### Ingest Content
```
@ingest <file> [--domain DOMAIN]
```

Or drop files in `wiki_system/inbox/` for automatic processing.

### Export
```
@export [format]
```

Formats: llms.txt, graph, json, sitemap

### Governance
```
@govern [check|rebuild-index|report]
```

## System Structure

```
wiki_system/
├── domains/           # Domain-specific wikis
│   ├── vulpine-solutions/
│   ├── home-assistant/
│   ├── homelab/
│   ├── personal/
│   └── general/
├── inbox/             # Drop files here for ingestion
├── index/             # Search indexes
├── exports/           # Generated exports
├── reports/           # Governance reports
├── logs/              # Daemon logs
└── state/             # System state
```

## Active Domains

- **vulpine-solutions**: MSP, operations, sales, security, client delivery
- **home-assistant**: Automation, voice assistant, ESP32, local AI, sensors
- **homelab**: Proxmox, k3s, storage, networking, GPUs, services
- **personal**: Family logistics, hobbies, plans, notes
- **general**: Fallback bucket for unclassified content

## Page Kinds

- **page**: Standard wiki page
- **entity**: People, organizations, technologies, tools
- **concept**: Ideas, methodologies, patterns
- **source**: Source documents

## Linking Conventions

Link to other pages using: `[[page-id]]`
Page IDs are kebab-case (e.g., `python-programming`, `api-design`)

## CLI Commands

```bash
# Initialize wiki
uv run llm-wiki init

# Search wiki
uv run llm-wiki search query "python"
uv run llm-wiki search get <page-id>

# Ingest content
uv run llm-wiki ingest file <file>
uv run llm-wiki ingest text "content" --domain <domain>

# Governance
uv run llm-wiki govern check
uv run llm-wiki govern rebuild-index

# Export
uv run llm-wiki export all
uv run llm-wiki export llmstxt
uv run llm-wiki export graph
```

